      "message": "Yes, but this makes the code a little bit more complicated, and this should not run very often anyway, so it\u0027s probably not worth it.\n\nNOTE: I have not covered the case where the write() returns a value that is smaller than kSize. In this case, the token is corrupted and should be erased (but this requires a new System::pathFileRemove() method) and some race condition. I believe the right way to do this is instead:\n\n  - Check if the file exists\n  - If it doesn\u0027t, create a new temporary file with the new content (and check it is written correctly)\n  - Atomic rename() / RenameFile() operation\n\nHowever, this is a little more complicated, and we should probably implement that through a generic helper class instead in the future.",
